The paper deals with the complexity of equivalence relations and languages, which are topics that fall under computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The use of automata and complexity measures also suggests a connection to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves the study of context-free and co-context-free languages, which are topics in formal language theory (cs.FL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the use of asymptotic analysis and complexity classes such as NP and BH$_2$ suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT).
